Yes. We should support all boundaries: {{left < X < right}}, {{left <= X right}}, {{left < X <= right}} and {{left <= X <= right}}

The default should be {{left <= X <= right}} like pandas and SQL's {{BETWEEN}}.

We can use {{FunctionOptions}} https://github.com/apache/arrow/blob/master/cpp/src/arrow/compute/function.h#L60 feature for it. For example, {{min_element_wise}} uses the {{FunctionOptions}} feature: https://github.com/apache/arrow/blob/master/cpp/src/arrow/compute/kernels/scalar_compare.cc
